title: Grateful Dead Live at Glens Falls Civic Center on 1981-05-05
lineage: Cassette Master (Nakamichi DR-1) > Korg MR-1000 (1-bit/5.6MHz) > Audiogate (1-bit/5.6MHz > 16-bit/44.1KHz) > cdwav (edits)
description:
Set 1

Feel Like A Stranger, Peggy-O-> El Paso, Ramble On Rose, CC Rider, Althea, Passenger, Brown Eyed Women, The Music Never Stopped-> Don't Ease Me In

Set 2

Scarlet Begonias-> Fire On The Mountain, Estimated Prophet-> Eyes Of The World-> Drums-> Uncle John's Band-> Truckin'-> Alabama Getaway-> Johnny B. Goode, E: U.S. Blues

Pitch sounds fine to me In fact it sounds about the same as the other recordings available. 

Nice FOB recording. Good work in the field. Nice show from an all-around good tour.
Solid Show Pitch is fine.. I recorded it too and it was a full speed ahead shown. The zippiness is more apparent being a closer to stage recording than most.  That building sounds like a cave..
